&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tuberculosis Advocate support worker &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 4 (subject to Agenda for Change Job Evaluation)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;30 hours per week (0.8 WTE)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a TB advocate support worker the post holder will work as a part of Tuberculosis (TB) Nursing Team who provides health care services for individuals affected by TB disease ensuring treatment completion.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a keen individual who has experience of working with vulnerable people (homeless people, people with alcohol &amp; or drug misuse, refugees, asylum seekers and people with no recourse to public fund, people with mental health issues those with language barrier to be part of the Community TB Team which is a multi-disciplinary team consist of TB Specialist Nurses, TB Advocacy Workers and administrators that work closely with the doctors in hospitals.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will act as a TB support worker under the supervision of the Tuberculosis Nurses to specific individuals; ensuring treatment completion, assessment of patient social and financial needs and work towards helping them get done.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post involves provision of directly observed therapy (DOT) in a variety of settings including patient’s homes, homeless hostels, GP surgeries etc. support in facilitating access to all primary healthcare services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will also link with the mobile screening unit when required. Many people who experience Tuberculosis are socially excluded and therefore this post will aim to improve access to all primary healthcare services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be flexible in approach to the clinical area, and have good numeric and literacy, IT skills as well as significant level of inter-personal skills and understanding of general medical terms.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be committed to quality, showing dignity, respect to colleagues and having trust and respect for all members of our teams.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Previous experience of working with patients affected by tuberculosis and the ability to speak a second language would be an asset.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For an informal discussion, please contact the following staff below:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;TB&lt;span&gt;Simin Mousavi&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; TB health &amp; social care advocacy worker Tel: 079 099 67 268 (Monday – Friday) 9:00 am- 5:00 pm&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Azhar Hammadi TB Health &amp; Social Care Advocacy Worker Mobile: 07880796571 (Wednesday –Friday) 9:00 am- 5:00 pm&lt;/p&gt;
